Kazakhstan announced Sunday that 14-day visa-free travel was granted for citizens of Iran, China and India. The unilateral 14-day visa-free travel took effect for personal, business and tourist purposes as of July 8, according to a statement by the countryâ€™s customs authority. However, visa-free stays cannot last more than 42 days in every 180 days, it added. Last month, Kazakhstan announced its plan to establish a visa-free regime with 100 countries.